<subSubSection id="C32D6512C049ED45BA8EFD0D9F222580" pageId="2" pageNumber="249" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B883699C049ED45BA8EFD0D9F222580" blockId="2.[226,1361,718,929]" pageId="2" pageNumber="249">
Comment: Originally described from Irkutsk in the Baikal region (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA64B68C049ED45BED8FD0D9F46252F" author="BERNHAUER M" pageId="2" pageNumber="249" pagination="78 - 79" refId="ref9130" refString="BERNHAUER M. (1910): Zur Staphylinidenfauna des palaearktischen Gebietes. - Societas Entomologica 25: 71 - 72, 78 - 79." type="journal article" year="1910">BERNHAUER 1910</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="4C374D1AC049ED45BB20FD319C5B252F" authorityName="BERNHAUER" authorityYear="1910" box="[332,571,754,782]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="249" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dimidiatipenne">
<emphasis id="B943EA8BC049ED45BB20FD319C5B252F" box="[332,571,754,782]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="249">L. dimidiatipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was subsequently reported from northeastern 
<collectingCountry id="F3207609C049ED45BE88FD319B31252F" box="[1252,1361,754,782]" name="Turkey" pageId="2" pageNumber="249">Anatolia</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="49F3F87BC049ED45BA87FCD49F002512" box="[235,352,791,819]" country="Turkey" name="Erzurum" pageId="2" pageNumber="249">Erzurum</collectingRegion>
: Tortum) by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA64B68C049ED45B87EFCD49C8B2512" author="COIFFAIT H" box="[530,747,791,819]" pageId="2" pageNumber="249" pagination="1 - 440" refId="ref9156" refString="COIFFAIT H. (1982): Coleopteres Staphylinidae de la region palearctique occidentale. IV. Sous famille Paederinae. Tribu Paederini 1 (Paederi, Lathrobii). - Nouvelle Revue d'Entomologie, Supplement 12 (4): 1 - 440." type="journal article" year="1982">COIFFAIT (1982)</bibRefCitation>
. However, no reference material was found in the Coiffait collection at the Muséum National d'Histoire Naturelle in Paris (TAGHAVIAN pers. comm.). It seems rather likely that the record in fact refers to 
<taxonomicName id="4C374D1AC049ED45BE0DFCA39B72255D" authorityName="KOCH" authorityYear="1937" box="[1121,1298,864,892]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="249" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bernhaueri">
<emphasis id="B943EA8BC049ED45BE0DFCA39B72255D" box="[1121,1298,864,892]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="249">L. bernhaueri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see below).
</paragraph>
